-0.01. By comparing our results with previous\nHARPS observations of classical Cepheids, we also point out a linear relation\nbetween the atmospheric velocity gradient and the amplitude of the radial\nvelocity curve. Moreover, we observe a phase shift (Van Hoof effect), whereas\nalpha Lup has no velocity gradient.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 31 May 2013 11:48:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-06-03"}
